# New Clinic — Cursor iOS / Mobile Scope

Use this with `new-clinic-big-picture-first.mdc` and `new-clinic-mobile-backend-gate.mdc`.

## Assume the device cannot

- Run XAMPP, Apache, or MySQL locally
- Watch `C:\xampp\apache\logs\error.log`
- Run long interactive terminal sessions reliably
- Hard-refresh and click through desks in the browser

Code on mobile; **verify on desktop or CI**.

## Safe on iOS (prefer these)

- React islands under `frontend/src/islands/`
- Shared UI under `frontend/src/components/`
- Island CSS (`main.css`, `desk-layout.css`)
- Docs under `Documentation/NewClinic/`
- Single-file PHP bugfixes with a clear, grep-able blast radius
- Config toggles and copy changes

## Avoid on iOS (defer to desktop)

- New service classes with deep dependency trees
- `AjaxController` constructor or import-list changes
- Multi-file PHP refactors in one session
- Constructor refactors across services (Windows stack-overflow risk)
- Deleting/renaming services while leaving `.broken` / `.bak` copies
- Merging large uncommitted batches across desks (registry + board + registration)

## End every mobile session with

1. **Push the branch** — do not leave hours of work only on the phone.
2. **Check CI** — workflow `New Clinic Verify` on the PR (PHP static + frontend test/build).
3. **Desktop gate (backend PHP touched)** — `composer verify:new-clinic` (includes AjaxController bootstrap).
4. **Desktop smoke (UI touched)** — hard-refresh, open one desk, confirm `ajax.php` actions return **200**.
5. **Asset version** — if frontend islands changed, bump `ModuleAssetVersion.php` once per batch.

Full checklist: `Documentation/NewClinic/new/MOBILE_IOS_CURSOR_CHECKLIST.md`

## When CI is red

Fix on desktop or in a follow-up mobile session scoped to the failure only.
Do not stack unrelated changes on top of a failing branch.

## Agent behavior on mobile

- Grep all call sites before editing (big-picture-first).
- List affected files when touching more than three files.
- State explicitly when verification could not run on this device.
- Never claim “done” for backend PHP without `composer verify:new-clinic` on desktop.
